                refrigerant levels can cause the system to struggle with heating
                or cooling, leading to higher energy consumption and increased
                wear on the compressor. Leaks can occur due to corrosion,
                damaged coils, or improper installation. Identifying and
                repairing refrigerant leaks requires specialized equipment and
                expertise, making it important to rely on a professional
                technician for this task. Regular inspections and maintenance
                can help detect and address refrigerant leaks early, ensuring
                the sustained performance and longevity of your heat pump.
              </p>

              <b>Electrical Issues</b>
              <p>
                Electrical issues can manifest in various forms, including
                malfunctioning thermostats, blown fuses, tripped circuit
                breakers, or damaged wiring. These problems can prevent the heat
                pump from operating correctly and pose safety hazards if not
                addressed promptly. Electrical issues can stem from age-related
                wear, improper installation, or external factors such as power
