                    <h3>
                      How do I reset my heat pump after a power outage?
                    </h3>
                  </div>

                  <div class="fa_plus">︾</div>

                  <div class="fa_minus">︽</div>
                </div>

                <div class="questions">
                  <p>Resetting your heat pump after a power outage is a straightforward process. Here’s a step-by-step guide to help you get your system running smoothly again:</p>
                  <ol>
                    <li>Turn Off the Thermostat: Begin by turning off your thermostat to prevent the heat pump from turning on during the reset process.</li>
                    <li>Locate the Reset Switch: Some heat pumps have a reset switch on the outdoor unit. If your unit has one, locate it. If not, you’ll need to reset the system via the circuit breaker.</li>
                    <li>Turn Off the Circuit Breaker: Find the circuit breaker that controls your heat pump and turn it off. This is usually located in your home's main electrical panel.</li>
                    <li>Wait: Leave the power off for about 5-10 minutes. This allows the system to fully reset.</li>
                    <li>Turn the Circuit Breaker Back On: After waiting, turn the circuit breaker back on to restore power to your heat pump.</li>
                    <li>Turn On the Thermostat: Finally, turn your thermostat back on and set it to your desired temperature. Your heat pump should start operating normally.</li>
                    <li>Check for Issues: After resetting, monitor your heat pump to ensure it’s functioning correctly. If you notice any unusual noises, insufficient heating or cooling, or error codes on the thermostat, there may be an underlying issue that needs professional attention.</li>
                  </ol>
                  <p>If your heat pump doesn’t resume normal operation after following these steps, it’s best to consult a professional. The technicians at Same Day Appliance Repair are experienced in diagnosing and fixing heat pump issues. Contact us for prompt and reliable service to get your system back in working order.</p>
